!! Basic dropzone with tiddler creation

```
<$file-dropzone actions="""
<$action-createtiddler
  $basetitle=<<filename>>
  _canonical_uri=<<canonical-uri>>
  _thumbnail_uri=<<generated-uri>>
  _content_hash=<<content-hash>>
  type=<<type>>
/>
""">
Drop files here
</$file-dropzone>
```

This creates a tiddler named after the file, with `_canonical_uri` pointing to the uploaded file on disk. If thumbnail generation is enabled, `_thumbnail_uri` points to the generated thumbnail.

!! Dropzone with custom tags and subfolder

```
<$file-dropzone subfolder="project-assets" actions="""
<$action-createtiddler
  $basetitle=<<filename>>
  _canonical_uri=<<canonical-uri>>
  tags="asset project"
  type=<<type>>
/>
""">
Drop project assets here
</$file-dropzone>
```

The `subfolder` attribute overrides the file-paths filter and places all uploads in `/files/project-assets/`.

!! Dropzone with target-prefix for nested paths

```
<$file-dropzone location="private-files" target-prefix="x/y/z" actions="""
<$action-createtiddler
  $basetitle=`$(target-prefix)$/$(filename)$`
  _canonical_uri=<<canonical-uri>>
  _thumbnail_uri=<<generated-uri>>
  _content_hash=<<content-hash>>
  type=<<type>>
  $savetitle="$:/temp/file-upload/last-created"/>
<$action-listops $tiddler="$:/temp/file-upload/recent"
  $subfilter="[{$:/temp/file-upload/last-created}]"/>
""">
Drop files here
</$file-dropzone>
```

The `target-prefix` attribute inserts a path prefix between the MIME-type subfolder and the filename. A file `photo.jpg` is placed at `images/x/y/z/photo.jpg` on disk. The prefix is also available as `<<target-prefix>>` in the action string for constructing the tiddler title.

